	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">UncleSporky wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Yeah, it's pretty clear that the engine is what you have when there is no audio data, graphical data, or level data.  You can't play an engine.</div>
<br />You can when it comes with a demo level made of pieces of the test case levels used in the engine's <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test-driven_development" class="postlink">test-driven development</a>. Technically, this is a game, but it's one that players expecting a more substantial game will call "steaming pile of tech demo".

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

